<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="106" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1428,2067]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,274,1428,1454]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Description</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[294,359,1428,1454]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1602,1624]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,314,1574]" captionTargetId="figure-93@2.[227,1361,314,1574]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Polycarpon tetraphyllum subsp. tetraphyllum. A: group of individuals growing in between paving slabs in Bogotá City (scale bar = 6 cm); B: general view (scale bar = 1 cm); leaves (scale bar = 0.3 cm); D: branch (scale bar = 0.3); E: inflorescence (scale bar = 0.3 cm); F: flower (scale bar = 0.3 cm)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5974061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5974061/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
):―Prostrate herbs, with a long principal root, branches bifurcate, internodes 
<quantity box="[1273,1384,1428,1455]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="7.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="4.0">4–10 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous. 
<emphasis box="[247,336,1464,1490]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Stipules</emphasis>
2–4 × 
<quantity box="[416,511,1464,1491]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
, two in each node, interpetiolar, triangular-deltoid or lanceolate, scarious, glabrous. 
<emphasis box="[136,214,1501,1526]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Leaves</emphasis>
4–8 × 
<quantity box="[293,389,1500,1527]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5 mm</quantity>
, opposite or verticillate, orbicular, ovate or slightly obovate, glabrous, bases attenuated, apices rounded or mucronate, pinnate nerviation with 2–4 pairs of secondary nerves; petiole ca. 
<quantity box="[1117,1182,1536,1563]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
, glabrous. 
<emphasis box="[1302,1452,1536,1562]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Inflorescence</emphasis>
up to 
<quantity box="[198,256,1572,1599]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
, terminal, cymose with numerous bracts in the nodes; similar to the stipules. 
<emphasis box="[1109,1201,1572,1598]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Flowers</emphasis>
<quantity box="[1207,1301,1572,1599]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
, pedicel ca. 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
, sepals five, 1–2 × 
<quantity box="[400,495,1608,1635]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
, subulate, margins hyaline; petaloid staminodes five, to 1 × 
<quantity box="[1170,1238,1608,1635]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
, oblong, with apex entire or slightly emarginate, white, shorter than the sepals; stamens 3–5, ca. 
<quantity box="[1008,1074,1644,1671]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long, white; filaments to 
<quantity box="[1365,1452,1644,1671]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
long; anthers 
<quantity box="[290,425,1680,1707]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3 mm</quantity>
long; ovoid, dorsifixed; ovary 
<quantity box="[776,872,1680,1707]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
, superous, ovoid; stile to 
<quantity box="[1160,1229,1680,1707]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
; stigma trifid. 
<emphasis box="[1394,1452,1681,1706]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Fruit</emphasis>
to 3 × 
<quantity box="[209,276,1716,1743]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
, capsule, with three valves. 
<emphasis box="[590,654,1716,1742]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Seeds</emphasis>
to 0.5 × 
<quantity box="[755,843,1716,1743]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
, semicircular, numerous; testa papillose.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="106" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1428,2067]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,441,1752,1778]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
― 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[470,753,1752,1778]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Polycarpon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tetraphyllum">
<emphasis box="[470,753,1752,1778]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Polycarpon tetraphyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is native to the mediterranean and it has spread in America, Africa, Asia, Europe and Oceania (
<bibRefCitation author="CABI" box="[528,670,1788,1814]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" refId="ref2791" refString="CABI (2021) Polycarpon tetraphyllum (fourleaf allseed). CAB International, Wallford. Available from: https: // www. cabi. org / isc / datasheet / 116427  tosummaryOfInvasiveness (accessed 16 January 2022)" type="url" year="2021">CABI, 2021</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[720,830,1788,1814]" name="Colombia" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Colombia</collectingCountry>
this species has only been collected in two localities of 
<collectingRegion box="[136,217,1824,1850]" country="Colombia" name="Bogota" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Bogotá</collectingRegion>
D.C (
<figureCitation box="[285,355,1824,1850]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,2029,2051]" captionTargetBox="[438,1152,960,1993]" captionTargetId="figure-339@3.[394,1193,945,2008]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution of the genus Polycarpon in Colombia. Blue square: P. tetraphyllum subsp. tetraphyllum; red diamond: P. apurense." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5974063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5974063/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="107" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1428,2067]" lastBlockId="2.[136,1452,158,293]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="107" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,1860,1886]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Notes:</emphasis>
― 
<taxonomicName box="[294,523,1860,1886]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Polycarpon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="apurese">
<emphasis box="[294,523,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Polycarpon apurese</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is currently the only native 
<taxonomicName box="[942,1073,1860,1886]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Polycarpon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[942,1073,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Polycarpon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxon occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[1305,1418,1860,1886]" name="Colombia" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, is naturally distributed in South America (
<collectingCountry box="[576,692,1896,1922]" name="Argentina" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[702,773,1896,1922]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[784,897,1896,1922]" name="Colombia" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[907,1012,1897,1923]" name="Paraguay" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1023,1122,1897,1923]" name="Uruguay" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1178,1297,1896,1922]" name="Venezuela" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bernal, R." box="[1307,1447,1896,1922]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" pagination="1043 - 1046" refId="ref2701" refString="Bernal, R. (2016) Cayophyllaceae. In: Bernal, R., Gradstein, S. R. &amp; Celis, M. (Eds.) Catalogo de plantas y liquenes de Colombia. Instituto de Ciencias Naturales, Universidad Nacional de Colombia, Bogota, pp. 1043 - 1046." type="book chapter" year="2016">Bernal 2016</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Munoz-Schick, M. &amp; Moreira-Munoz, A. &amp; de Trenqualye, A." box="[136,435,1932,1959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" pagination="467 - 470" refId="ref3993" refString="Munoz-Schick, M., Moreira-Munoz, A. &amp; de Trenqualye, A. (2016) Polycarpon moreiranum, nueva especie de Caryophyllaceae endemica de Chile. Gayana Botanica 73 (2): 467 - 470. https: // doi. org / 10.4067 / S 0717 - 66432016000200467" type="journal article" year="2016">
Muñoz-Schick 
<emphasis box="[310,360,1932,1958]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="POWO" box="[448,606,1932,1958]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" refId="ref4073" refString="POWO (2019) Plants of the World Online. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew. Available from: http: // www. plantsoftheworldonline. org / (accessed 16 January 2022)." type="url" year="2019">POWO, 2019</bibRefCitation>
), whereas it has been introduced in 
<collectingCountry box="[1018,1104,1932,1958]" name="Mexico" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Escamilla, M." box="[1119,1300,1932,1958]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" pagination="123 - 126" refId="ref2970" refString="Escamilla, M. (1999) Nuevos registros de Caryophyllaceae para Mexico. Polibotanica 10: 123 - 126." type="journal article" year="1999">Escamilla 1999</bibRefCitation>
). Despite not included in the molecular analyses by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kool, A. &amp; Bengtson, A. &amp; Thulin, M." box="[567,771,1968,1994]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" pagination="775 - 782" refId="ref3692" refString="Kool, A., Bengtson, A. &amp; Thulin, M. (2007) Polyphyly of Polycarpon (Caryophyllaceae) inferred from DNA sequence data. Taxon 56 (3): 775 - 782. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 25065860" type="journal article" year="2007">
Kool 
<emphasis box="[630,687,1968,1994]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">et al.</emphasis>
(2007)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1823" box="[783,913,1969,1994]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Polycarpon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="apurense">
<emphasis box="[783,913,1969,1994]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">P. apurense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows, in our opinion, all the characters typical of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ascherson &amp; Schweinfurt" baseAuthorityName="Forsskal" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[167,317,2005,2030]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Polycarpon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="prostratum">
<emphasis box="[167,317,2005,2030]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">P. prostratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and three Macaronesian species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1792" box="[832,975,2004,2030]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Polycarpaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[832,975,2004,2030]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">Polycarpaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Volponi, C. R." box="[989,1145,2004,2030]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref4386" refString="Volponi, C. R. (2004) Espermatologia y palinologia de las especies de Polycarpon (Caryophyllaceae) en la Argentina. Physis (Buenos Aires), Seccion C 59 (136 - 137): 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="2004">Volponi 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
